spanishExample: ¡Sal y llama a tu padre! El policía ya está aquí.
englishTranslation: Go out and call your father! The police officer is already here.

spanishExample: ¡Sal! Te tiene que parecer una buena idea.
englishTranslation: Go out! It has to seem like a good idea to you.

spanishExample: ¡Salga! Hay nueve o diez personas aquí.
englishTranslation: (formal) Go out! There are nine or ten people here.

spanishExample: ¡Salga! Lo llamaré cuando tenga tiempo.
englishTranslation: (formal, masculine) Go out! I will call you when I have time.

spanishExample: ¡Salgamos! El rey no parece triste.
englishTranslation: Let’s go out! The king doesn’t seem sad.

spanishExample: ¡Tiene que salir rápido!
englishTranslation: It has to come out fast!

spanishExample: ¿Me puedes llamar después? Estoy con ocho amigas ahora.
englishTranslation: Can you call me later? I’m with eight friends(f) now.

spanishExample: ¿Por qué la llamas ahora? Ayer salimos con ella.
englishTranslation: Why are you calling her now? Yesterday we went out with her.

spanishExample: ¿Sales con alguien que se llama Martín?
englishTranslation: Do you go out with someone that is called Martín?

spanishExample: ¿Sales todos los días a esa hora?
englishTranslation: Do you go out every day at that time?

spanishExample: Alguien está llamando a la puerta, ¡salgan!
englishTranslation: Someone is knocking at the door, go out! (plural)

spanishExample: Cinco menos dos son tres.
englishTranslation: Five minus two is three.

spanishExample: Él es un maestro de esas diez cosas.
englishTranslation: He is a master of those ten things.

spanishExample: El presidente y la reina nos parecen malas personas.
englishTranslation: The president and the queen seem to us like bad people.

spanishExample: El profesor ha salido, pero el agente aún está aquí.
englishTranslation: The professor has gone out, but the agent is still here.

spanishExample: Ella no nos llamó a tiempo y ahora queremos que salgan.
englishTranslation: She didn’t call us on time and now we want them to go out.

spanishExample: Ellos salen con esas diez personas.
englishTranslation: They go out with those ten people.

spanishExample: La llama todos los días porque tiene nueve años.
englishTranslation: She calls her every day because she is nine years old.

spanishExample: Los llamo ahora porque él salió sin decirles.
englishTranslation: I’m calling them now because he went out without telling them.

spanishExample: Me parecía que él había llamado al doctor.
englishTranslation: It seemed to me that he had called the doctor.

spanishExample: No estamos saliendo estos días.
englishTranslation: We aren’t going out these days.

spanishExample: No pareces estar bien, voy a ir contigo, pero salgo en una hora.
englishTranslation: You don’t seem to be fine, I’m going to go with you, but I leave in an hour.

spanishExample: No quieren que él salga por nueve horas.
englishTranslation: They don’t want him to go out for nine hours.

spanishExample: Nos ha parecido un buen maestro.
englishTranslation: He has seemed to us like a good teacher.

spanishExample: Nos pareció una buena idea que él salga esta noche.
englishTranslation: It seemed to us like a good idea that he go out tonight.

spanishExample: Ocho menos dos son seis.
englishTranslation: Eight minus two are six.

spanishExample: Ocho menos siete es uno.
englishTranslation: Eight minus seven is one.

spanishExample: Ocho menos uno son siete.
englishTranslation: Eight minus one is seven.

spanishExample: Quieren que salgamos por ocho horas.
englishTranslation: They want us to go out for eight hours.

spanishExample: Salimos ayer, pero ella sale hoy porque es la jefa.
englishTranslation: We went out yesterday, but she goes out today because she’s the boss.

spanishExample: Seis más uno son siete.
englishTranslation: Six plus one is seven.

spanishExample: Siete más tres son diez.
englishTranslation: Seven plus three is ten.

spanishExample: Tres más dos son cinco.
englishTranslation: Three plus two is five.

spanishExample: Vamos a salir de fiesta este fin de semana.
englishTranslation: We’re going to go out partying this weekend.

spanishExample: Yo salí el fin de semana y por eso lo llaman ahora.
englishTranslation: I went out on the weekend and that’s why they are calling him now.
